<HEADLINE>
FT  20 AUG 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equities Futures and Options Trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The expiry of the August index options was the main feature in an otherwise
lacklustre session in the derivatives, writes Joel Kibazo.
The mid-morning expiry was without incident and total volume in the sector
came to 34,232, of which 16,679 was done in the FT-SE 100 option and 7,923
in the Euro FT-SE option. Dixons was the busiest stock option with a total
of 1,334 lots dealt.
In futures, volume in the September contract on the FT-SE 100 was 10,415
lots as it ended the session at 3,208, up 9 on its previous close.
