<HEADLINE>
FT  20 AUG 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Wool prices have continued to advanced on a broad front, and as auctions
have been resumed in the new selling season the pace has tended to
accelerate. There are variations between sectors. Finer merinos are in short
supply, and remaining stocks held in the official Australian stockpile are
low. Demand meanwhile is building up with fashion one factor, and
anticipation of shortages to come another. The world crossbred wool
situation is also obviously firmer with supplies and stocks seen as liable
to fall short of demand. Only with middle micron merinos is the Australian
stockpile seen as a holding factor, and this is not enough to prevent price
rises here also. Wool international's Eastern states market indicator closed
706 cents yesterday, compared with 693 a week ago. The spices report was not
available for this edition.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P0214 Sheep and Goats.
</IN>
<XX>
