<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 94 / World Commodities Prices: Copper price break-out fails -
Market report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
failure of the three months delivery COPPER price to maintain an early
afternoon break through resistance around Dollars 2,420 a tonne injected
some caution into late trading at the London Metal Exchange.
'Most metals looked strong in the first rings (organised trading sessions)
but when copper fell back it brought out profit-taking and buyers backed
off,' a trader said.
NICKEL was again a busy market as it continued its upward correction after
the past month's heavy losses.
Three months ALUMINIUM reached Dollars 1,493 a tonne as the market continued
its recent steady advance off support which had built around Dollars 1,470.
Compiled from Reuter
</TEXT>
