<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 94 / International Capital Markets: Moody's lifts Westpac debt
rating to A-1
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Moody's has raised the long-term senior debt rating of Westpac, one the 'big
four' Australian banks, to A-1 from A-2, writes Nikki Tait in Sydney. The
subordinated debt rating was also improved from to A-2 from A-3. About
ADollars 3.2bn of securities are affected.
Moody's said the upgrade reflected Westpac's improving asset quality,
earnings and capital levels. It said these positive trends should continue
in the medium term, reinforced by Australia's favourable economic
conditions.
Although the banking sector generally suffered badly during the recent
recession, Westpac - with heavy exposures to the property market - was among
the worst affected.
</TEXT>
