<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 94 / Observer: Cold comfort
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An American woman has won Dollars 2.9m damages because her McDonald's coffee
was hot. She had put the cup between her legs - to remove the cap - but it
spilt and she suffered serious burns. The jury said it wanted not just to
award appropriate damages, but also to deliver a message to the fast food
industry. Said the foreman: 'The coffee's too hot out there . . .'
</TEXT>
