<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 94 / Letters to the Editor: Inefficiency for all to see
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr RICHARD SIMMONS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I note that the Post Office is planning to show full programmes to
queueing customers ('Post Office queues to get piped TV shows', August 16).
A queue is the classical method used by an inefficient monopoly to ration
supply. Any other business would see a liability rather than a marketing
asset. This is evidence to support depriving the Post Office of its
monopolies, with or without privatisation.
Richard Simmons,
lower ground floor,
7 Palace Court,
London W2 4LP
</TEXT>
