<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 94 / London Stock Exchange: P&amp;O firm
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, CHRISTOPHER PRICE, JOEL KIBAZO and SAQIB QURESHI
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Rumours of a profits upgrade in transport and property group P&amp;O sent the
shares 14 ahead to 704p in trading volume of 4.7m.
The talk suggested that a leading broker was about to raise its full-year
profits estimate to match BZW's top of the range Pounds 375m prediction.
However, none of the names cited as possible candidates for the upgrade
would confirm such a move.
Sentiment in the stock was further lifted by reports of a Smith New Court
recommendation, and a favourable outlook for container shipping from P&amp;O's
Dutch rival Nedlloyd. The group reported disappointing interims but
mentioned stable rates and growing volumes on its north Atlantic and Far
East routes on which it competes with P&amp;O.
